article.headline: Brown 69, Cornell 64
article.story: ITHACA, N.Y. (AP) -- Scott Friske scored 23 points to lead Brown to a 69-64 win over Cornell on Saturday night. Damon Huffman made four 3-pointers and finished with 14 points. Keenan Jeppesen added 10 points and eight rebounds for the Bears (9-16, 5-7 Ivy), who shot 59 percent from the floor. The lead changed 14 times in the first half, but Brown was up 36-35 at the break. The Bears took the lead for good on a three-point play by Friske with 7:19 to play. Cornell (11-15, 6-6) got two chances to tie with less than two minutes left, but shots by Ryan Rourke and Adam Gore rimmed out. Lenny Collins led the Big Red, who were held to 33 percent shooting in the second half, with 18 points. Gore added 14 points and Rourke had 11.
